column5: Yup---True  Course I'm guilty----I wouldn't want my kids doin some of the crazy things I did
We were tough kids back in '48 and didn't need any girly helmets when we rode our scooters
In my era,we rode bicycles with no helmets  I think we were just a little to crazy lol.
We were tough kids back in '48 and didn't need any girly helmets when we rode our scooters   Har dee har--..He(you?) is lower to the ground than standing up!! Not much dist to fall!!
It's now 100% certain Lew has never smiled in a photograph, ever!
It's now 100% certain Lew has never smiled in a photograph, ever! lol

I remember those days..... the trips to the summer camp in the back of the station wagon, no seat belts, carbon monoxide rushing in the rolled down tailgate window (and before unleaded gasoline at that), fighting with your brother. The gear was in the back seat to give us room to burn off  energy, and the parents some noise reduction. That's when the channel changer wasn't a box, it was  the smallest person in the room........
